Now we are going to compare the 40mm lens, with the Canon 35mm and the Canon 50mm

00:04:27.500 --> 00:04:31.000
which are all widely used for street photography

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:34.000
I am going to start with the 35mm

00:04:35.500 --> 00:04:38.500
Then I am going to try with the 40mm,

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:44.400
which to me is very good for street pictures,

00:04:44.500 --> 00:04:49.000
because it is quite close to human sight

00:04:49.200 --> 00:04:55.000
(varies between 35mm and 55mm)

00:04:59.100 --> 00:05:02.700
And now the 50mm

00:05:09.200 --> 00:05:12.200
Clearly, you can see a difference

00:05:12.700 --> 00:05:15.800
At 50mm, I feel like we are a little bit too zoomed in,

00:05:15.900 --> 00:05:20.500
while at 40mm, I have a pretty accurate view of

00:05:20.500 --> 00:05:23.000
what I am actually seeing with my eyes right now

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.400
You just saw with Merwen how the 40mm 
looked on a full frame sensor camera,

00:05:28.400 --> 00:05:32.700
Now we are going to take a glimpse at the 
way it looks on an APS-C sensor

00:05:39.400 --> 00:05:45.300
The 40mm is more accurate than the 50mm in terms
of how close it gets to the human sight

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:51.000
It is very enjoyable for street photography

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:02.000
Depth of field looks good

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:06.400
High quality look

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:16.000
Resolution is very clear

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:19.600
And I like the minimum focus distance (30cm/11,8 inches)

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
This pancake lens is very small, so you can take it anywhere with you

00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:30.000
And you can keep a low profile with it,

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:37.500
which makes it great for street pictures
(or in places where taking pictures is prohibited)

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:44.000
To conclude, I would say this lens has many qualities

00:06:46.800 --> 00:06:49.300
The silent autofocus,

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:54.000
Its size : it's light, small and you can take it anywhere.

00:06:55.500 --> 00:06:58.000
You could even fit it in your pocket !

00:06:59.500 --> 00:07:02.100
I would advise it to travelers, or street photograhers,

00:07:02.100 --> 00:07:06.800
For portraits, it might be a bit too short of
 a focal length, but you can make it work,

00:07:06.800 --> 00:07:11.000
in particular with editorial portraits, in which you have 
to include a little bit more details about the environment

00:07:11.800 --> 00:07:16.000
For this type of focal length, we are usually
used to bigger apertures, such as f/1.2 or f/1.4,

00:07:17.500 --> 00:07:20.700
But I think that 2.8 can be a good 
compromise for many travelers

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.000
I hope you enjoyed this test

